39 /* Peripheral: AAR */
40 /* Description: Accelerated Address Resolver. */
41 
42 /* Register: AAR_INTENSET */
43 /* Description: Interrupt enable set register. */
44 
45 /* Bit 2 : Enable interrupt on NOTRESOLVED event. */
46 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
47 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
48 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
49 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
50 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Set (1UL)
52 /* Bit 1 : Enable interrupt on RESOLVED event. */
53 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
54 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos)
55 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
56 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
57 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Set (1UL)
59 /* Bit 0 : Enable interrupt on END event. */
60 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
61 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos)
62 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
63 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
64 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
66 /* Register: AAR_INTENCLR */
67 /* Description: Interrupt enable clear register. */
68 
69 /* Bit 2 : Disable interrupt on NOTRESOLVED event. */
70 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
71 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
72 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
73 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
74 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
76 /* Bit 1 : Disable interrupt on RESOLVED event. */
77 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
78 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos)
79 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
80 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
81 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
83 /* Bit 0 : Disable interrupt on ENDKSGEN event. */
84 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
85 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
86 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
87 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
88 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
90 /* Register: AAR_STATUS */
91 /* Description: Resolution status. */
92 
93 /* Bits 3..0 : The IRK used last time an address was resolved. */
94 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos (0UL)
95 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Msk (0xFUL << AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos)
97 /* Register: AAR_ENABLE */
98 /* Description: Enable AAR. */
99 
100 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable AAR. */
101 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
102 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
103 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0x00UL)
104 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (0x03UL)
106 /* Register: AAR_NIRK */
107 /* Description: Number of Identity root Keys in the IRK data structure. */
108 
109 /* Bits 4..0 : Number of Identity root Keys in the IRK data structure. */
110 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos (0UL)
111 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Msk (0x1FUL << AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos)
113 /* Register: AAR_POWER */
114 /* Description: Peripheral power control. */
115 
116 /* Bit 0 : Peripheral power control. */
117 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Pos (0UL)
118 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_POWER_POWER_Pos)
119 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Disabled (0UL)
120 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Enabled (1UL)
123 /* Peripheral: ADC */
124 /* Description: Analog to digital converter. */
125 
126 /* Register: ADC_INTENSET */
127 /* Description: Interrupt enable set register. */
128 
129 /* Bit 0 : Enable interrupt on END event. */
130 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
131 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_INTENSET_END_Pos)
132 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
133 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
134 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
136 /* Register: ADC_INTENCLR */
137 /* Description: Interrupt enable clear register. */
138 
139 /* Bit 0 : Disable interrupt on END event. */
140 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
141 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
142 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
143 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
144 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
146 /* Register: ADC_BUSY */
147 /* Description: ADC busy register. */
148 
149 /* Bit 0 : ADC busy register. */
150 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Pos (0UL)
151 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Pos)
152 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Ready (0UL)
153 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Busy (1UL)
155 /* Register: ADC_ENABLE */
156 /* Description: ADC enable. */
157 
158 /* Bits 1..0 : ADC enable. */
159 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
160 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
161 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0x00UL)
162 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (0x01UL)
164 /* Register: ADC_CONFIG */
165 /* Description: ADC configuration register. */
166 
167 /* Bits 17..16 : ADC external reference pin selection. */
168 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_Pos (16UL)
169 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_Pos)
170 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_None (0UL)
171 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_AnalogReference0 (1UL)
172 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_AnalogReference1 (2UL)
174 /* Bits 15..8 : ADC analog pin selection. */
175 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Pos (8UL)
176 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Msk (0xFFUL << ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Pos)
177 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Disabled (0UL)
178 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput0 (1UL)
179 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput1 (2UL)
180 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput2 (4UL)
181 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput3 (8UL)
182 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput4 (16UL)
183 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput5 (32UL)
184 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput6 (64UL)
185 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput7 (128UL)
187 /* Bits 6..5 : ADC reference selection. */
188 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_Pos (5UL)
189 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_Pos)
190 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_VBG (0x00UL)
191 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_External (0x01UL)
192 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_SupplyOneHalfPrescaling (0x02UL)
193 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_SupplyOneThirdPrescaling (0x03UL)
195 /* Bits 4..2 : ADC input selection. */
196 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_Pos (2UL)
197 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_Msk (0x7UL << ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_Pos)
198 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_AnalogInputNoPrescaling (0x00UL)
199 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_AnalogInputTwoThirdsPrescaling (0x01UL)
200 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_AnalogInputOneThirdPrescaling (0x02UL)
201 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_SupplyTwoThirdsPrescaling (0x05UL)
202 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_SupplyOneThirdPrescaling (0x06UL)
204 /* Bits 1..0 : ADC resolution. */
205 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_Pos (0UL)
206 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_CONFIG_RES_Pos)
207 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_8bit (0x00UL)
208 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_9bit (0x01UL)
209 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_10bit (0x02UL)
211 /* Register: ADC_RESULT */
212 /* Description: Result of ADC conversion. */
213 
214 /* Bits 9..0 : Result of ADC conversion. */
215 #define ADC_RESULT_RESULT_Pos (0UL)
216 #define ADC_RESULT_RESULT_Msk (0x3FFUL << ADC_RESULT_RESULT_Pos)
218 /* Register: ADC_POWER */
219 /* Description: Peripheral power control. */
220 
221 /* Bit 0 : Peripheral power control. */
222 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Pos (0UL)
223 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_POWER_POWER_Pos)
224 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Disabled (0UL)
225 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Enabled (1UL)
